  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6784.96 sitting just below the 6785 GEX wall (+55B) and near the flip strike at 6780, dealers are in active hedging mode as long gamma holders. The massive positive gamma concentration from 6785-6800 (+91B at 6800) creates a strong magnetic pull, with dealers likely selling delta into any push toward these levels while providing support on dips toward 6770 (-15B negative gamma). The recent GEX surge amplifies this dynamic, suggesting dealers will aggressively fade moves away from the 6780-6785 equilibrium zone.\n\n**Bottom line: expect price to get pulled back toward 6780-6785 with limited breakout potential above 6800.**",
